ut intimacy, power, and privilege, this book offers an innovative framework for understanding the status of non-monogamy in Western society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMonogamous relationshipsxSocial aspects. 7aFAMILY & RELATIONSHIPS / Alternative Family.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015z978311127703508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311142000440uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482898740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774828987423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774828987/original  a978-3-11-127402-7  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-127703-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-142000-4  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles